Last Updated: February 2025
This Notice describes the privacy practices of the Polaris
family of brands
and companies, such as Polaris Off-Road; Polaris On-Road (including Indian Motorcycle); Polaris Marine; Polaris Adventures; Polaris Xchange; Kolpin; Pro Armor; Trail Tech; 509; and KLIM (collectively, “Polaris,” “we,” “our,” and “us”). We respect your privacy and value our relationship with you.
This Polaris Privacy Notice (“Notice”) describes how we collect, use, and share your information when you use or interact with us through: our websites, mobile applications, or online services (the “Sites”); and other offline methods, such as in person, by telephone, or at events. It also covers information we receive from our dealers, distributors, service providers, business partners, and other third-party sources. Certain Polaris Sites, vehicles, products, and services may be subject to other privacy notices that are separate from or supplement this Notice, and are provided on or with the relevant Sites, vehicles, products, or services. For example, our RIDE COMMAND services, are subject to our
RIDE COMMAND Privacy Notice
.
